<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Basically the market for leveraged loans was v=
ery good at the beginning of 2022, and pretty bad as we near the end of 202=
2, so a lot of banks signed up to do a lot of buyout loans in 2022 that the=
y ended up being unable to sell on decent terms. If you are a bank, you hav=
e to decide whether to sell your loans now, at a loss, or hold on to them a=
nd hope the price goes back up. This is an economic decision =E2=80=94=C2=
=A0like any other trading decision =E2=80=94=C2=A0though it also has an acc=
ounting component; if you don=E2=80=99t=C2=A0<em>try=C2=A0</em>to sell the =
loans then you don=E2=80=99t know how much money you=E2=80=99ve lost. Also =
there are some year-end issues to consider. <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bl=
oombergbusiness.com/click/29848628.258549/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvb=
S9uZXdzL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjItMTEtMjkvYmFua3Mtc3R1Y2std2l0aC00Mi1iaWxsaW9uLWRl=
YnQtc2VpemUtY2hhbmNlLXRvLW9mZmxvYWQtaXQ_Y21waWQ9QkJEMTEzMDIyX01PTkVZU1RVRkY=
mdXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291cmNlPW5ld3NsZXR0ZXImdXRtX3Rlcm09MjIxMTMwJn=
V0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN0dWZm/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBf8f562c5" itemprop=
=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #0=
00000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-b=
ottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">=
  Anyway</a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Banks in the US and Europe with around $42 bil=
lion of buyout debt stuck on their balance sheets are making the most of th=
eir last chance to get rid of it this year.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Stabilization in the leveraged loan and high y=
ield bond markets has led to an opening for deals -- including for bonds an=
d loans tied to the buyout of TV ratings business Nielsen Holdings Plc -- a=
s banks try to reduce debt on their balance sheets before the holidays. Off=
loading the so-called hung debt, even at steep discounts, confines losses t=
o this financial year while also appeasing risk departments and regulators.=
 =E2=80=A6</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CIf the window is open for these hung =
deals, you will see the banks jump through it because the window is not ope=
n for every deal,=E2=80=9D said Bill Zox, portfolio manager at Brandywine G=
lobal Investment Management. =E2=80=9CAnd it could shut again at any time.=
=E2=80=9D</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Hung debt has been a big problem for Wall Stre=
et this year. Banks have taken huge mark-to-market losses on deals they und=
erwrote before a rapid rise in interest rates crushed funding markets and t=
he threat of recession quashed investor demand for riskier assets. With tha=
t backdrop, stabilization of leveraged loan prices -- which recently recove=
red to an average of close to 93 cents on the dollar in the US, according t=
o index data -- has created a fertile ground for deals.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Still, while some debt is being offloaded, mor=
e recent buyouts are adding to the pile, including about $13 billion of fin=
ancing related to Elon Musk=E2=80=99s acquisition of Twitter and, more rece=
ntly, a private equity buyout of a majority stake in Roper Technologies Inc=
.=E2=80=99s industrial operations business.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Around here, I have eyes only for that Twitter=
 Inc. debt. I have <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click=
/29848628.258549/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLz=
IwMjItMTEtMDEvcGVvcGxlLXdpbGwtcGF5LWZvci1pbGxpcXVpZGl0eT9jbXBpZD1CQkQxMTMwM=
