he reputation of, like, centralized cryptocurrency shadow banks. This has a=
lmost nothing to do with the question of whether a blockchain is a good dat=
abase architecture for stock exchanges or property registers or shipping. B=
ut if you announced a blockchain project in 2018, and by 2020 you realized =
it wasn=E2=80=99t going anywhere, 2022 is a good year to formally kill it. =
